# SOP discovery (on demand)

**When the operator asks about a program/chapter/topic** and the correct SOP is not already in the thread starter or continuity brief:

```bash
python scripts/resolve_sop.py --topic "<phrase>" --json
python scripts/resolve_sop.py --chapter <chapter_id> --json
python scripts/resolve_sop.py --module <module_id> --json
python scripts/resolve_sop.py --role <operator|charter|ide_build|explore|neutral> --json
python scripts/resolve_sop.py --list-topics --json
```

**Execute `next_action` and load only paths in `load_always` / `load_for_build` for the thread role.**

| Thread role | Load from resolve JSON |
|-------------|------------------------|
| **charter** | `load_always` only |
| **ide_build** | IDE_BUILD_STARTER only — ignore resolve unless generating starter |
| **operator** | `OPERATOR_STATUS` + continuity brief; resolve for ad-hoc topics |
| **explore / neutral** | User @ scope only |

**Archive catalog:** [`ARCHIVE_INDEX.md`](../../docs/SOP/ARCHIVE_INDEX.md) — archived chapters only; **do not load for BUILD**.

**Charter / neutral:** discovery only — no relay, no branch recovery ([`ppe-thread-roles.mdc`](ppe-thread-roles.mdc))

**Operator:** may read `OPERATOR_STATUS.md` after role is confirmed

Do **not** treat stale handoff copies as SSOT when generated files disagree — prefer `ACTIVE_PRODUCT_DIRECTION.json`, manifest, queue

Index: [`CHAPTER_DOC_INDEX.json`](../../docs/SOP/CHAPTER_DOC_INDEX.json) · canon: [`AGENT_ROUTING_V1.md`](../../docs/SOP/AGENT_ROUTING_V1.md)

Maintenance (backfill archived evidence YAML, READY starter regen incl. stale doc-resolve, coordination repair): `sop_discovery_maintenance.cmd --all --apply`
